2
00:01:55,156 --> 00:01:58,523
嘿,妈妈。妈妈!看那。
Hey, Mama. Mom! Look at that.

3
00:01:59,861 --> 00:02:01,294
看,妈妈,你看。
Look, Mommy, look.

4
00:02:11,538 --> 00:02:12,664
约翰尼!
Johnny!

5
00:02:33,995 --> 00:02:36,792
现在你让妈妈做代言人。记住。
Now you let Mommy do the talking. Remember.

6
00:02:37,198 --> 00:02:38,323
是的,妈妈。
Yes, Mom.

7
00:02:42,569 --> 00:02:44,230
但他没有马。
But he has no horse.

8
00:02:44,704 --> 00:02:45,898
没有说话。
No talking.

9
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:07,691
早上好。
Good morning.

10
00:03:08,361 --> 00:03:10,352
-你看起来像你有麻烦。 - 是的。
- You look like you've had trouble. - Yep.

11
00:03:10,463 --> 00:03:13,796
我失去了我的马前几天远离一些印度人。
I lost my horse a few days ago getting away from some Indians.

12
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:14,958
印度人吗?
Indians?

13
00:03:15,468 --> 00:03:18,232
我们昨晚干营Ilano之上。
We made dry camp last night above the Ilano.

14
00:03:19,239 --> 00:03:22,538
萨姆在这里闻起来更阿帕奇人,蹭我。
Sam here smelled more Apaches, nuzzled me up.

15
00:03:22,676 --> 00:03:24,735
所以我想把一些我们之间的距离。
So I thought I'd put some miles between us.

16
00:03:24,844 --> 00:03:26,869
但是为什么呢?我们在和平与Apache。
But why? We're at peace with the Apache.

17
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:28,641
- 我们有一个条约。 - 是的,夫人。
- We have a treaty. - Yes, ma'am.

18
00:03:28,748 --> 00:03:32,149
现在我必须把我的新马,借或买一个。
Now I got to get me a new horse, borrow or buy one.

19
00:03:32,319 --> 00:03:36,550
我可以支付你在美国的脚本。我骑调度一般骗子。
I can pay you in United States script. I'm riding a dispatch for General Crook.

20
00:03:37,123 --> 00:03:39,990
- 我的名字叫巷。 - 我是劳夫人。
- My name's Lane. - I'm Mrs. Lowe.

21
00:03:40,327 --> 00:03:41,589
我是强尼。
I'm Johnny.

22
00:03:41,795 --> 00:03:44,696
- 水看起来诱人。 - 嗯,帮助自己。
- The water sure looks inviting. - Well, help yourself.

23
00:03:44,798 --> 00:03:46,629
当心那只狗,儿子。
Watch out for that dog, son.

24
00:03:47,366 --> 00:03:50,302
你能雇佣我或给我一匹马,罗伊太太吗?
Could you hire me or sell me a horse, Mrs. Lowe?

25
00:03:50,403 --> 00:03:54,533
当然。我只有耕马,和两只活。
Of course. I've only got plow horses, and two that are only half-broken.

26
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:58,507
打破他们的手为我是受伤了,不得不去城镇。
The hand that was breaking them for me got hurt and had to go to town.

27
00:04:00,347 --> 00:04:03,281
- 你的意思是你住这儿吗?-哦,不。
- You mean you're staying here alone? - Oh, no.

28
00:04:03,617 --> 00:04:05,846
不,我的丈夫是在山上……
No, my husband is up in the hills...

29
00:04:05,952 --> 00:04:07,976
- 工作一些牛。-哦。
- working some cattle. - Oh.

30
00:04:08,088 --> 00:04:11,353
他会挑选今天要离开,当我们有一个客人。
He would pick today to be away, when we have a visitor.

31
00:04:11,557 --> 00:04:13,422
我喜欢认识他,夫人。
I'd enjoy meeting him, ma'am.

32
00:04:16,595 --> 00:04:19,792
我不会碰那只狗,儿子。他不需要爱抚。
I wouldn't touch that dog, son. He don't take to petting.

33
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:24,302
现在如果你会允许,夫人,我就看看那些马。
And now if you'll allow, ma'am, I'll take a look at those horses.

34
00:04:24,403 --> 00:04:27,167
当然。你会发现一个鞍的谷仓。
Of course. You'll find a saddle over by the barn.

35
00:04:27,506 --> 00:04:31,102
与此同时,我将给你点吃的。我想象你饿了。
In the meantime, I'll fix you something to eat. I imagine you're hungry.

36
00:04:31,210 --> 00:04:32,838
我可以吃。谢谢你！
I could eat. Thank you.

37
00:05:08,314 --> 00:05:12,444
我很抱歉我的丈夫不得不选择今天去打猎的那些失去了小牛。
I'm so sorry my husband had to pick today to go hunting those lost calves.

38
00:05:19,024 --> 00:05:21,618
他很有可能会喜欢有一个人说话。
He would have enjoyed having a man to talk to.

39
00:05:22,494 --> 00:05:24,257
我们欢迎游客。
We welcome visitors.

40
00:05:25,030 --> 00:05:28,124
在这里Ionely肯定是正确的。尤其对一个女人。
Must be right Ionely around here. Especially for a woman.

41
00:05:28,233 --> 00:05:30,394
我不介意。我在这里长大。
I don't mind. I was raised here.

42
00:05:31,570 --> 00:05:34,470
- 我可以喂你的狗吗? - 没有,谢谢。
- What can I feed your dog? - Nothing, thanks.

43
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:38,335
他做了他自己。可以超越任何在兔子的领土。
He makes out by himself. Can outrun any rabbit in the territory.

44
00:05:38,444 --> 00:05:40,344
一点儿也不麻烦。
It's no trouble at all.

45
00:05:42,314 --> 00:05:45,874
如果你不介意,太太,我宁愿你没有喂他。
If you don't mind, ma'am, I'd rather you didn't feed him.

46
00:05:46,618 --> 00:05:50,247
我看到。你不想让他得到进食的习惯从别人。
I see. You don't want him to get in the habit of taking food from anyone else.

47
00:05:50,356 --> 00:05:52,220
嗯,你可以把这个交给他。
Well, you can hand it to him.

48
00:05:52,524 --> 00:05:56,460
不,小姐,我不让他吃,要么。山姆的独立。
No, ma'am, I don't feed him, either. Sam's independent.

49
00:05:56,695 --> 00:05:59,630
他不需要任何人。我希望他能保持这种方式。
He doesn't need anybody. I want him to stay that way.

50
00:05:59,931 --> 00:06:01,263
这是一个好方法。
It's a good way.

51
00:06:02,434 --> 00:06:06,164
- 每个人都需要别人。 - 是的,夫人。大多数人。
- Everyone needs someone. - Yes, ma'am. Most everyone.

52
00:06:06,271 --> 00:06:07,636
太糟糕了,不是吗?
Too bad, isn't it?

53
00:06:08,107 --> 00:06:10,040
- 你是一个好厨师,夫人。 - 谢谢你。
- You're a good cook, ma'am. - Thank you.

54
00:06:10,141 --> 00:06:13,543
一个女人应该是一个好厨师。好厨师自己。
A woman should be a good cook. Good cook myself.

55
00:06:41,739 --> 00:06:43,707
你为什么不让他当他被卡住了?
Why didn't you get on him when he was stuck?

56
00:06:43,808 --> 00:06:47,300
因为我不想让他坐在我从一站开始。
'Cause I didn't want him sitting on me from a standing start.

57
00:06:47,645 --> 00:06:49,078
同他住。
Stay with him.

58
00:07:23,948 --> 00:07:26,075
你选择了最野蛮的人。
You chose the most savage one.

59
00:07:26,384 --> 00:07:28,113
我不会给你一个论点。
I won't give you an argument there.

60
00:07:28,219 --> 00:07:29,709
他一直都是一个斗士。
He's always been a fighter.

61
00:07:29,821 --> 00:07:32,948
我不会给一个插镍为马,不会打架。
I wouldn't give a plugged nickel for a horse that wouldn't fight.

62
00:07:33,057 --> 00:07:35,525
它让你失望当情况变得艰难。
It lets you down when the going gets tough.

63
00:07:36,828 --> 00:07:38,193
有点单调。
It's a little dull.

64
00:07:38,295 --> 00:07:41,163
嗯,我可以做几乎任何事情在一个牧场,但我永远不可能…
Well, I can do almost everything around a ranch, but I never could...

65
00:07:41,665 --> 00:07:43,099
把一个边缘一把斧头。
put an edge on an axe.

66
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,326
它在哪儿呢?
Where is it?

67
00:07:44,702 --> 00:07:46,863
-什么? - 的磨刀石。
- What? - The grindstone.

68
00:07:59,484 --> 00:08:01,883
这个农场看起来像是这里一会儿。
This ranch looks like it's been here a little while.

69
00:08:01,985 --> 00:08:05,443
是的,我出生在这里。我的丈夫在这里长大,太。
Yes, I was born here. My husband was raised here, too.

70
00:08:07,157 --> 00:08:10,491
他是一个孤儿。他的父母被杀在马车队屠杀……
He's an orphan. His parents got killed in a wagon-train massacre...

71
00:08:10,594 --> 00:08:12,289
所以我父亲带他在。
so my father took him in.

72
00:08:12,863 --> 00:08:14,922
-方便。-你什么意思?
- Handy. - What do you mean?

73
00:08:15,999 --> 00:08:18,490
好吧,看来这个数字是反对它。
Well, it seems the figures are against it.

74
00:08:19,369 --> 00:08:22,338
只有轻的研究员在1000平方英里…
Only young fellow in 1,000 square miles...

75
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:26,004
只有轻的女孩在1000平方英里。
only young girl in 1,000 square miles.

76
00:08:26,443 --> 00:08:30,515
他们会在旋转中超过对方。这就是我的意思。方便的。
They get in a whirl over each other. That's what I meant. Handy.

77
00:08:31,014 --> 00:08:33,176
我想这是一个巧合。
I guess it was quite a coincidence.

78
00:08:33,650 --> 00:08:38,246
但是他们说正确的两人要满足的命运的安排。
But they say that the right two people are going to meet by an arrangement of destiny.

79
00:08:38,789 --> 00:08:40,653
你相信,洛太太吗?
You believe that, Mrs. Lowe?

80
00:08:41,191 --> 00:08:43,716
- 是的,我喜欢。 - 有趣。
- Yes, I do. - Interesting.

81
00:08:52,536 --> 00:08:56,597
总是沉叶片成日志,儿子。使边缘清洁。
Always sink a blade into a log, son. Keeps the edge clean.

82
00:08:57,774 --> 00:09:00,902
嗯,我想我最好退出失速,回到那匹马。
Well, I guess I'd better quit stalling and get back to that horse.

83
00:09:01,011 --> 00:09:02,706
和我可以玩山姆现在?
And can I play with Sam now?

84
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,311
我已经告诉你两次不来。
I've told you twice not to.

85
00:09:05,415 --> 00:09:07,406
但是你做你想做的。
But you do what you wanna do.

86
00:09:18,728 --> 00:09:21,561
真的,莱恩先生,如果你知道这狗会咬人,我想……
Really, Mr. Lane, if you knew the dog would bite, I should think...

87
00:09:21,664 --> 00:09:25,294
罗伊太太,人学习让钻头。轻人刚学。
Mrs. Lowe, people learn by getting bit. Youngster just learned.

88
00:09:26,936 --> 00:09:28,029
约翰尼。
Johnny.

89
00:09:32,242 --> 00:09:35,769
不要碰那个狗了!现在进去把你的小睡。
Don't you ever touch that dog again! Now go in and take your nap.

90
00:10:17,053 --> 00:10:19,748
而我在这,我将鞋这些犁马。
While I'm at it, I'll shoe those plow horses.

91
00:10:20,255 --> 00:10:23,053
非常感谢你。他们需要一个修蹄,我猜。
Thank you very much. They do need a shoeing, I guess.

92
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:24,353
他们做的。
They do.

93
00:10:25,061 --> 00:10:28,895
我想我的丈夫的很难找到那些迷路的小腿。
I guess my husband's having a hard time finding those strayed calves.

94
00:10:29,231 --> 00:10:30,493
我猜他是。
I guess he is.

95
00:10:31,334 --> 00:10:33,802
也许他不会回家直到今晚……
Perhaps he won't be home until late tonight...

96
00:10:33,903 --> 00:10:38,498
或者他可能连山上的营地中,明天来在你死后。
or he may even camp in the hills and come in tomorrow after you're gone.

97
00:10:39,008 --> 00:10:42,944
他会因此很抱歉错过我们的一个很少有偶尔的来访者。
He'll be so sorry to have missed one of our very few occasional visitors.

98
00:10:45,714 --> 00:10:47,944
我想我要去照顾约翰尼。
I guess I'll go and look after Johnny.

99
00:10:48,184 --> 00:10:50,117
罗伊太太,你是一个骗子。
Mrs. Lowe, you're a liar.

100
00:10:51,186 --> 00:10:54,212
- 和一个全能的可怜的骗子。-我不懂你。
- And an almighty poor liar. - I don't understand you.

101
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:57,154
这些马没有穿鞋的一两个月。
These horses haven't been shod in a couple of months.

102
00:10:57,259 --> 00:11:00,353
这是小事一桩,斧还没有优势,在两个月。
It's a cinch that axe hasn't had an edge on it in two months.

103
00:11:00,462 --> 00:11:04,296
和你的茶可以,5磅的茶可以在你的房子是空的。
And your tea can, a five-pound tea can in your house is empty.

104
00:11:04,633 --> 00:11:06,862
你的丈夫已经消失了很长一段时间。
Your husband's been gone a long time.

105
00:11:06,969 --> 00:11:09,733
现在,看这里,莱恩先生,我不认为你有任何权利……
Now, look here, Mr. Lane, I don't think you have any right to...

106
00:11:09,838 --> 00:11:12,466
我不谈论权利。我所说的谎言。
I'm not talking about rights. I'm talking about lies.

107
00:11:12,573 --> 00:11:14,439
你为什么对我撒谎,罗伊太太吗?
Why did you lie to me, Mrs. Lowe?

108
00:11:14,543 --> 00:11:18,502
是你害怕,也许你就不会和我在这儿安全与你的丈夫了吗?
Were you afraid that maybe you wouldn't be safe here with me with your husband away?

109
00:11:18,614 --> 00:11:21,447
- 它吗? - 这部分是它。
- That it? - That's partly it.

110
00:11:21,884 --> 00:11:24,910
女人总是图每一个男人的出现希望他们。
Women always figure every man comes along wants them.

111
00:12:22,977 --> 00:12:24,842
-雷恩。 - 是的,夫人?
- Mr. Lane. - Yes, ma'am?

112
00:12:25,346 --> 00:12:27,838
你是对的。我在撒谎。我的丈夫是过期。
You're right. I was lying. My husband is overdue.

113
00:12:27,949 --> 00:12:29,416
他应该回家很久以前。
He should have been home long ago.

114
00:12:29,517 --> 00:12:31,348
图阿帕奇人杀了他?
Figure Apaches killed him?

115
00:12:31,452 --> 00:12:34,182
当然不是。有一百个可能的解释。
Of course not. There are a hundred possible explanations.

116
00:12:34,288 --> 00:12:35,812
印度人是其中之一。
Indians are one of them.

117
00:12:35,922 --> 00:12:38,255
但是我们在和平与Apache,除了少数……
But we're at peace with the Apache, except for a few...

118
00:12:38,359 --> 00:12:40,122
罗伊太太,如果你有良好的感觉……
Mrs. Lowe, if you've got good sense...

119
00:12:40,228 --> 00:12:43,129
你会收拾你和那个男孩的你跟我出来。
you'll pack up you and that boy of yours and come out with me.

120
00:12:43,231 --> 00:12:45,631
那是在酝酿麻烦在Apache的小屋。
There's trouble brewing in the Apache lodges.

121
00:12:45,733 --> 00:12:48,463
维托利奥,他们主要的首席,称为战争委员会。
Vittorio, their main chief, called a war council.

122
00:12:48,603 --> 00:12:51,299
一个完整的报告是在分派我携带。
A full report of it is in that dispatch I'm carrying.

123
00:12:51,405 --> 00:12:55,341
但是你不知道,我们一直相处得壮观与Apache。
But you don't know, we've always gotten along splendidly with the Apache.

124
00:12:56,110 --> 00:12:58,704
他们喝酒,把他们的马,我们的春天……
They drink and bring their horses to our spring...

125
00:12:58,813 --> 00:13:01,144
在北到野牛追捕。
on their way north to the buffalo hunt.

126
00:13:01,449 --> 00:13:05,647
我从没见过伟大的维托利奥,但已经足够的阿帕奇人这里。
I've never seen the great Vittorio, but there've been plenty of Apaches here.

127
00:13:06,821 --> 00:13:10,416
我看到伟大的维托利奥,在本条约。
I've seen the great Vittorio, before the treaty.

128
00:13:14,362 --> 00:13:16,989
他的马已经40头皮挂在它的鬃毛。
His horse had 40 scalps hung in its mane.

129
00:13:17,098 --> 00:13:18,861
这是以前的条约。
That was before the treaty.

130
00:13:20,034 --> 00:13:22,433
我们打破了该条约,美国白人。
We broke that treaty, us Whites.

131
00:13:22,837 --> 00:13:26,932
没有的话在Apache语言撒谎,并且他们被骗了。
There's no word in the Apache language for lie, and they've been lied to.

132
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:29,174
如果它们上升,不会有……
If they rise, there won't be...

133
00:13:29,276 --> 00:13:32,302
- 一个白左在领土。 - 他们不会打扰我。
- a White left in the territory. - They won't bother me.

134
00:13:32,445 --> 00:13:35,244
我们,我的意思是。我们总是相处得很好。
Us, I mean. We always got along very well.

135
00:13:35,715 --> 00:13:38,912
我认识的人,男人和他的妻子相处真正好……
People I know, man and his wife, got along real well for...

136
00:13:39,719 --> 00:13:41,688
20。然后有一天……
20 years. Then one day...

137
00:13:42,622 --> 00:13:44,317
她增加了一个大洞,在他…
she upped and blew a hole in him...

138
00:13:44,425 --> 00:13:46,985
大到足以驱动一辆公共马车通过。
big enough to drive a stagecoach through.

139
00:13:47,494 --> 00:13:50,190
她疯了。阿帕切人疯了。
She got mad. The Apaches are mad.

140
00:13:50,331 --> 00:13:52,730
好吧,我没有什么好担心的,我肯定。
Well, I have nothing to worry about, I'm sure.

141
00:13:54,435 --> 00:13:55,992
很高兴被确定。
Nice to be sure.

142
00:13:59,272 --> 00:14:00,706
让开。
Get out of the way.

143
00:14:01,641 --> 00:14:04,439
- 奇怪的狗你有。 - 我没有他。
- Strange dog you have. - I don't have him.

144
00:14:04,878 --> 00:14:07,847
- 你们两个在一起。 - 他依然和我在一起。
- The two of you are together. - He stays with me.

145
00:14:08,515 --> 00:14:12,815
- 他可以闻到了印度在半英里。 - 他气味印第安人吗?我不相信它。
- He can smell an Indian at a half a mile. - He smells Indians? I don't believe it.

146
00:14:13,019 --> 00:14:15,817
当然,很多狗闻到印第安人。你可以教他们。
Sure, lots of dogs smell Indians. You can teach them.

147
00:14:15,922 --> 00:14:17,253
教他们吗?如何?
Teach them? How?

148
00:14:17,357 --> 00:14:19,951
首先你准备一个小狗,然后……
First you get yourself a puppy and then...

149
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:23,687
你雇佣自己一个驯服的印度和削减一个柳树开关。
you hire yourself a tame Indian and cut a willow switch.

150
00:14:23,864 --> 00:14:25,492
然后你得到印度打小狗……
Then you get the Indian to beat the puppy...

151
00:14:25,599 --> 00:14:27,897
与柳开关四到五次一天。
with a willow switch four or five times a day.

152
00:14:28,001 --> 00:14:31,801
当他长大了,他会总是信号当他闻到一个印度。
And when he grows up, he'll always signal when he smells an Indian.

153
00:14:31,905 --> 00:14:34,169
打一只小狗。多么残忍。
Beat a puppy. How cruel.

154
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:36,236
这是他们的方式做它。
That's the way they do it.

155
00:14:36,376 --> 00:14:38,708
无论如何,我不相信狗能闻到印第安人。
Anyway, I don't believe a dog can smell Indians.

156
00:14:38,812 --> 00:14:40,972
我的意思是,不同于其他任何人。
I mean, as different from anyone else.

157
00:14:41,081 --> 00:14:42,878
- 你或我,例如。 - 好吧,他们可以。
- You or me, for instance. - Well, they can.

158
00:14:42,983 --> 00:14:45,076
作为一个事实,印度人能闻到白人。
As a matter of fact, Indians can smell White people.

159
00:14:45,185 --> 00:14:47,483
- 我不相信它。 - 好吧,这是真的。
- I don't believe it. - Well, it's true.

160
00:14:48,188 --> 00:14:52,386
我有部分印度,我能闻到你当我顺风的你。
I'm part Indian, and I can smell you when I'm downwind of you.

161
00:14:55,028 --> 00:14:59,465
- 那是不可能的。 - 不,它不是不可能的,劳夫人。
- That's impossible. - No, it isn't impossible, Mrs. Lowe.

162
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:10,700
你烤的今天。我可以闻到新鲜的面包在你。
You baked today. I can smell fresh bread on you.

163
00:15:13,113 --> 00:15:15,604
今天你煮的某个时候和咸肉。
Sometime today you cooked with salt pork.

164
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:17,844
闻,你,太。
Smell that on you, too.

165
00:15:18,984 --> 00:15:20,850
你闻起来都像肥皂。
You smell all over like soap.

166
00:15:21,121 --> 00:15:24,749
你洗个澡。和最重要的是,你闻起来都像一个女人。
You took a bath. And on top of that, you smell all over like a woman.

167
00:15:26,226 --> 00:15:30,457
我能找到你在黑暗中,罗伊太太,我只有部分印度。
I could find you in the dark, Mrs. Lowe, and I'm only part Indian.

168
00:16:12,071 --> 00:16:13,732
罗伊太太。
Mrs. Lowe.

169
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:18,708
你想要什么?
What do you want?

170
00:16:19,011 --> 00:16:22,640
- 我浇水和粒度的股票。 - 谢谢你。
- I watered and grained the stock. - Thank you.

171
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:25,849
我将睡在附近某处今晚。
I'll bed down near here someplace tonight.

172
00:16:28,420 --> 00:16:29,614
Lane先生吗?
Mr. Lane?

173
00:16:34,727 --> 00:16:37,821
你不能在外面过夜,暴风雨就要来了。
You can't sleep outside, there's a storm coming.

174
00:16:37,962 --> 00:16:40,430
我已经修正了托盘给你在角落里。
I've fixed a pallet for you in the corner.

175
00:16:47,473 --> 00:16:50,965
这将是未开化的让任何人睡在外面……
It would be uncivilized to let anyone sleep outside...

176
00:16:51,075 --> 00:16:53,544
毕竟,我们是文明的,不是吗?
and after all, we are civilized, aren't we?

177
00:16:53,645 --> 00:16:56,204
为你说话,当然。但我呢?
Speaking for you, of course. But me?

178
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:59,177
我猜你会叫我文明。
I guess you could call me civilized.

179
00:17:01,754 --> 00:17:05,849
那是你的床。我很抱歉必须在地板上。
That's your bed. I'm sorry it has to be on the floor.

180
00:17:07,825 --> 00:17:12,525
我已经设置为早上面糊。我希望不会打扰你的噪音。
I have to set the batter for the morning. I hope the noise won't disturb you.

181
00:17:12,898 --> 00:17:14,160
它不会。
It won't.

182
00:17:17,336 --> 00:17:18,768
晚上好,夫人。
Good night, ma'am.

183
00:17:41,292 --> 00:17:42,658
你把枪放下。
Put that gun down.

184
00:17:46,832 --> 00:17:48,822
你是本州巷,枪手。
You're Hondo Lane, the gunman.

185
00:17:49,934 --> 00:17:52,562
- 我带着枪。 - 别再接近。
- I carry a gun. - Don't come any nearer.

186
00:17:53,304 --> 00:17:55,568
你杀了三个人在去一场枪战。
You killed three men in a gunfight last year.

187
00:17:55,673 --> 00:17:58,141
- 我们听说过。三个男人。 - 是的,夫人。
- We heard about it. Three men. - Yes, ma'am.

188
00:17:58,342 --> 00:18:01,140
- 就像快我可以。 - 别再接近。
- Just as quick as I could. - Don't come any nearer.

189
00:18:03,581 --> 00:18:06,448
这不是一个好主意点这些东西之一在任何人……
It's not a very good idea to point one of these things at anybody...

190
00:18:06,551 --> 00:18:09,042
用一个空腔在撞针。
with an empty chamber under the firing pin.

191
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:11,185
你可以看到它像天纯。
You can see it plain as day.

192
00:18:11,889 --> 00:18:14,084
我保持这种方式,因为约翰尼。
I keep it that way because of Johnny.

193
00:18:14,659 --> 00:18:15,956
嗯,现在它的加载。
Well, now it's loaded.

194
00:18:16,627 --> 00:18:19,391
保持这种方式,保持高。
Keep it that way, and keep it high.

195
00:18:30,808 --> 00:18:34,141
请留下来。我真的想要你。
Please stay. I really want you to.

196
00:18:35,379 --> 00:18:39,577
我很抱歉。我应该意识到从一开始,你是一个绅士。
I'm sorry. I should have realized from the beginning that you are a gentleman.

197
00:18:45,523 --> 00:18:48,356
文明吗?绅士?
Civilized? Gentleman?

198
00:18:50,460 --> 00:18:52,224
嗯,很多一天。
Well, a lot for one day.

199
00:18:58,201 --> 00:18:59,566
晚上,女士。
Night, ma'am.

200
00:19:19,257 --> 00:19:22,021
早.... 早起。
Morning. Getting an early start.

201
00:19:23,528 --> 00:19:26,087
一定要告诉那个小男人再见我。
Be sure and tell that little man goodbye for me.

202
00:19:26,197 --> 00:19:28,664
我应该叫醒他向你告别。
I ought to wake him to say goodbye to you.

203
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:30,823
这是我,我让他睡。
Was it me, I'd let him sleep.

204
00:19:30,934 --> 00:19:34,371
轻人成长睡觉,但是你做你想做的事。
Youngsters grow sleeping, but you do what you want to.

205
00:19:35,640 --> 00:19:38,073
他是如此的高兴,你为他吹口哨。
He was so delighted with that whistle you made for him.

206
00:19:38,175 --> 00:19:42,237
很高兴听到它。他和我相处很好。
Glad to hear it. He and I got along just fine.

207
00:19:42,480 --> 00:19:46,540
它更像是一个比一个哨子吹长笛。它的范围几乎完整的规模。
It's more like a flute than a whistle. It ranges almost the full scale.

208
00:19:46,883 --> 00:19:50,046
我学会了让他们当我是活在Mescalero。
I learned to make them when I was living with the Mescalero.

209
00:19:50,153 --> 00:19:53,122
我的妻子用来使他们对每个孩子都在小屋。
My squaw used to make them for every kid in the lodge.

210
00:19:54,157 --> 00:19:57,388
- 你住与Apache吗?- 5。
- You lived with the Apache? - Five years.

211
00:19:57,661 --> 00:20:01,358
- 和你有一个印度的妻子吗? - 妻子,妻子...
- And you had an Indian wife? - Wife, squaw<i>...</i>

212
00:20:01,831 --> 00:20:06,234
我随意的借几英尺的绳索从,线圈在披屋。
I took the liberty of borrowing a few feet of rope off of that coil in the lean-to.

213
00:20:06,736 --> 00:20:10,001
- 为它付你钱的,如果你让我。 - “当然不。
- Gladly pay you for it, if you let me. - 'Course not.

214
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:12,833
今天的山是如此美丽。
The hills are so beautiful today.

215
00:20:13,443 --> 00:20:16,276
怎么奇怪清楚他们总是在沙尘暴。
Odd how clear they always are after a dust storm.

216
00:20:19,248 --> 00:20:22,582
一定是很有趣的生活与Apache。
Must have been very interesting living with the Apache.

217
00:20:22,886 --> 00:20:24,182
我很喜欢它。
I liked it.

218
00:20:25,254 --> 00:20:29,748
- 这个印度的妻子你有...。- 她死了。
- This Indian wife you have<i>...</i> - Had. She's dead.

219
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:33,186
我很抱歉。我不是有意要抚养一个不愉快的回忆。
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to bring up an unhappy memory.

220
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:40,670
我不记得任何事情Destarte不满。
I can't remember anything unhappy about Destarte.

221
00:20:41,605 --> 00:20:45,597
Destarte吗? 怎样的音乐。这意味着什么呢?
Destarte? How musical. What does it mean?

222
00:20:47,344 --> 00:20:51,781
你不能说它在Mescalero除外。这意味着早上。
You can't say it except in Mescalero. It means morning.

223
00:20:53,083 --> 00:20:55,243
但这并不意味着什么,要么。
But that isn't what it means, either.

224
00:20:56,018 --> 00:20:59,921
不仅仅意味着,。印度的字的意思是声音和…
Means more than just that. Indian words mean the sound and...

225
00:21:00,389 --> 00:21:02,085
一个单词的感觉,就像……
feel of a word, like...

226
00:21:02,892 --> 00:21:05,792
黎明,第一个青铜灯……
crack of dawn, the first bronze light...

227
00:21:06,363 --> 00:21:09,456
这使山丘坚决反对灰色的沙漠。
that makes the buttes stand out against the gray desert.

228
00:21:10,299 --> 00:21:12,564
你听到的第一个声音的一条小溪……
The first sound you hear of a brook...

229
00:21:12,701 --> 00:21:15,363
在一些岩石冰壶,鲑鱼跳跃。
curling over some rocks, with trout jumping.

230
00:21:16,538 --> 00:21:19,599
这就像当你起床在第一光……
It's like when you get up in the first light...

231
00:21:19,908 --> 00:21:24,242
只有你和她,你离开一个窝棚。
just you and her and you go out of a wickiup.

232
00:21:25,447 --> 00:21:29,680
它闻起来种烟熏和私人,只有你和她,……
Where it smells kind of smoky and private, just you and her, and...

233
00:21:30,719 --> 00:21:32,983
种安全只有你们两个。
kind of safe with just the two of you.

234
00:21:34,189 --> 00:21:35,656
站在外面……
Stand outside and...

235
00:21:36,158 --> 00:21:39,788
觉得咬下来的第一个风从高分裂……
feel the bite of the first wind coming down from the high divide...

236
00:21:40,729 --> 00:21:42,458
承诺的降雪。
that promises snowfall.

237
00:21:45,134 --> 00:21:48,228
不能用英语说,但那是她的名字。
Can't say it in English, but that was her name.

238
00:21:49,571 --> 00:21:50,765
Destarte。
Destarte.

239
00:21:53,275 --> 00:21:57,268
- 你让我想起她一些。 - 印度的一个女孩?
- You remind me of her some. - Of an Indian girl?

240
00:21:57,780 --> 00:21:59,270
她是公平的吗?
Was she fair?

241
00:21:59,481 --> 00:22:01,915
她的头发是黑如10英尺下降。
Her hair was black as 10 feet down.

242
00:22:02,351 --> 00:22:05,752
你有没有看到一只乌鸦的翅膀,黑色和闪闪发光的吗?
Did you ever see a crow's wing, how black and gleaming it is?

243
00:22:05,854 --> 00:22:08,049
- 是的。 - 她的头发擦过。
- Yes. - That's the way her hair shined.

244
00:22:09,358 --> 00:22:10,950
我想付你的绳索。
I'd like to pay you for that rope.

245
00:22:11,060 --> 00:22:14,086
骑调度,我有权给美国脚本。
Riding dispatch, I have the right to give U.S. Script.

246
00:22:14,830 --> 00:22:18,322
- 你爱她吗? - 我不知道。
- You loved her? - I don't know.

247
00:22:19,668 --> 00:22:20,965
我需要她。
I needed her.

248
00:22:25,507 --> 00:22:29,170
- 但如果她是黑暗和我公平… - 为什么你让我想起她吗?
- But if she was dark and I'm fair... - Why you reminded me of her?

249
00:22:29,311 --> 00:22:31,643
- 是的。 - 我不知道。
- Yes. - I don't know.

250
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:35,111
我想到它。你看起来不像她的东西。
I thought about it. You don't look anything like her.

251
00:22:35,551 --> 00:22:38,748
我完全意识到我是一个平凡的女人,雷恩。
I am fully aware that I am a homely woman, Mr. Lane.

252
00:22:38,853 --> 00:22:40,343
我不是那个意思。
I didn't mean that.

253
00:22:40,456 --> 00:22:43,856
我有一个坏习惯,实话实说。但漂亮并不多。
I have a bad habit of telling the truth. But being pretty isn't much.

254
00:22:43,958 --> 00:22:45,950
我知道很多漂亮的人我不会相信……
I know a lot of pretty people I wouldn't trust...

255
00:22:46,060 --> 00:22:48,153
与一个被镀镍手表。
with a busted nickel-plated watch.

256
00:22:48,364 --> 00:22:51,492
但是另外一些人,出来的东西里,……
But some others, something comes out of the inside of them and...

257
00:22:52,133 --> 00:22:53,931
你知道你可以信任他们。
you know you can trust them.

258
00:22:54,470 --> 00:22:56,232
Destarte过。
Destarte had that.

259
00:22:57,473 --> 00:22:59,373
和你有它,太。
And you've got it, too.

260
00:23:03,578 --> 00:23:07,015
- 我是一个已婚女人。 - 我考虑到这一点了。
- I'm a married woman. - I thought about that, too.

261
00:23:07,582 --> 00:23:10,380
我想我吻了你,因为你让我想起Destarte。
I guess I kissed you because you remind me of Destarte.

262
00:23:10,518 --> 00:23:12,680
或许这是因为我讨厌觉得你的头发…
Or maybe it was because I hate to think of your hair...

263
00:23:12,787 --> 00:23:15,312
挂在中心杆的一个Apache简陋的小屋。
hanging from the center pole of an Apache wickiup.

264
00:23:16,524 --> 00:23:18,924
嗯,很久以前我让我一个规则。
Well, a long time ago I made me a rule.

265
00:23:19,894 --> 00:23:22,192
我让人们做他们想做的事。
I let people do what they want to do.

266
00:23:25,199 --> 00:23:26,666
山姆!
Sam!

267
00:23:33,307 --> 00:23:35,468
你是一个奇怪的男人,雷恩。
You are a strange man, Mr. Lane.

268
00:23:36,210 --> 00:23:39,646
我不知道。再见,劳夫人。
I don't know about that. Goodbye, Mrs. Lowe.

269
00:24:52,252 --> 00:24:55,085
- 你是维托利奥。 - 我是维托利奥。
- You are Vittorio. - I am Vittorio.

270
00:24:56,190 --> 00:24:58,420
你的马在这里被淡化。
Your horses have been watered here.

271
00:24:58,959 --> 00:25:01,928
- 你被告知去。 - 我不能离开。
- You were told to go. - I couldn't leave.

272
00:25:02,362 --> 00:25:05,490
我的丈夫不在,我不认为我 …
My husband is away, and I didn't think that I<i>...</i>

273
00:25:09,871 --> 00:25:12,601
你的人在这里水他们的马。
Your people water their horses here.

274
00:25:16,878 --> 00:25:18,674
你离开我的母亲独自一人。
You leave my mother alone.

275
00:25:55,181 --> 00:25:57,513
阻止他!阻止他!
Stop him! Stop him!

276
00:26:11,531 --> 00:26:15,092
-我不是害怕你。 - 你不恐惧Apache吗?
- I ain't scared of you. - You're not fear Apache?

277
00:26:18,104 --> 00:26:19,502
没有。
No.

278
00:26:19,906 --> 00:26:23,705
他害怕伤害到母亲,但不是自我。
He fear hurt to mother, but not that to self.

279
00:26:25,612 --> 00:26:28,206
他勇敢的。像Apache的男孩。
He brave. Like Apache boy.

280
00:26:36,222 --> 00:26:39,748
他现在结拜兄弟。我叫他小战士。
Him now blood brother. I call him Small Warrior.

281
00:26:39,859 --> 00:26:42,554
他属于月亮狗旅馆,Chiricahua Apache。
Him belong Moon Dog Lodge, Chiricahua Apache.

282
00:26:42,662 --> 00:26:46,564
你照顾他。你现在的母亲Chiricahua战士。
You care for him well. You now mother Chiricahua warrior.

283
00:26:46,766 --> 00:26:48,256
安全的生活在这里。
Live safely here.

284
00:26:50,936 --> 00:26:54,134
我希望有一天,有人与你的儿子。
I hope someday, someone befriends your sons.

285
00:26:54,273 --> 00:26:57,572
我的儿子已经死了。白人杀死他们。
My sons are dead. White man kill them.

286
00:28:32,104 --> 00:28:35,972
认为你的头皮会被悬挂在一些Apache窝棚现在。
Figured your scalp would be hanging in some Apache wickiup by now.

287
00:28:36,074 --> 00:28:38,703
- 嗨,水牛。 - 是在下注。
- Hi, Buffalo. - Been making bets on it.

288
00:28:38,810 --> 00:28:42,644
- 你肯定失望的我,本州。 - 你想赢得你的打赌。
- You're sure a disappointment to me, Hondo. - You like to win your bet.

289
00:28:43,048 --> 00:28:44,742
我穿了一些马匹。
I wore out some horses.

290
00:28:44,883 --> 00:28:47,942
你穿着你当你是在它。在这里,让我得到这个。
You wore out you while you was at it. Here, let me get that.

291
00:28:48,053 --> 00:28:50,953
这是哪里的水吗?
Where's that water?

292
00:28:54,992 --> 00:28:57,359
- 看起来像我打赌,水牛。 - 嗨,迪克。
- Looks like I won a bet, Buffalo. - Hi, Dick.

293
00:28:57,462 --> 00:28:59,624
是的,我欠你一壶红眼。
Yeah, I owe you a jug of red-eye.

294
00:28:59,731 --> 00:29:04,327
- 这感觉很好。 - 有次当水是好的。
- This feels good. - There's times when water is good.

295
00:29:10,007 --> 00:29:11,566
这正是我的意思。
That's exactly what I mean.

296
00:29:11,676 --> 00:29:14,042
我说我有权利在这里谈谈弓收缩的主要…
I say I got a right to talk to this here bow-necked Major...

297
00:29:14,145 --> 00:29:16,545
- 我不要跟没有下属。 - 主要的睡着了。
- I don't talk to no underlings. - Major's asleep.

298
00:29:16,647 --> 00:29:19,445
这只是他太差劲了。我是一个公民,我想去看他。
That's just too bad about him. I'm a citizen and I want to see him.

299
00:29:19,550 --> 00:29:21,643
主要不是也没睡三天。
Major ain't had any sleep for three days.

300
00:29:21,753 --> 00:29:23,983
我可以告诉你一切一样他可以。
I can tell you everything just as well as he can.

301
00:29:24,088 --> 00:29:26,522
我们不是没接到了北。
We ain't heard nothing from up north.

302
00:29:27,290 --> 00:29:30,556
如果你问我,骑兵的害怕维托利奥。我认为美国骑兵……
If you ask me, the Cavalry's scared of Vittorio. I think the U.S. Cavalry...

303
00:29:30,660 --> 00:29:34,256
我非常喜欢你的观点的美国骑兵。
I am greatly interested in your opinion of the United States Cavalry.

304
00:29:34,365 --> 00:29:36,594
继续, Mr... 无论你的名字是。
Continue, Mr<i>...</i> Whatever your name is.

305
00:29:37,033 --> 00:29:39,161
骑兵应该支持定居者。
The Cavalry is supposed to support the settlers.

306
00:29:39,270 --> 00:29:40,999
我有一些牛在北边,我不打算……
I've got some cattle up north, I don't intend...

307
00:29:41,105 --> 00:29:44,802
C队伍正在扫描到北护送出任何移民他们可能发现。
C troop is making a sweep to the north to escort out any settlers they may find.

308
00:29:45,710 --> 00:29:49,840
C一个多星期队伍是现在晚在返回。那是我能告诉你。
C troop is now over a week late in returning. That's all I can tell you.

309
00:29:50,148 --> 00:29:52,013
C队伍不会回来。
C troop isn't coming back.

310
00:30:00,624 --> 00:30:02,786
我很感激,先生,如果你将离开。
I'd be obliged, sir, if you would leave.

311
00:30:02,893 --> 00:30:04,418
一个好业务,整个领地……
A fine business, the whole territory...

312
00:30:04,528 --> 00:30:05,893
,长官! - 得到!
- Sergeant! - Get!

313
00:30:12,602 --> 00:30:14,696
滚开,你这个肮脏的…
Get out of the way, you mangy<i>...</i>

314
00:30:17,942 --> 00:30:21,377
- 如果这是你的坏蛋,让他出。-走在他周围。
- lf that's your cur, get him out of the way. - Walk around him.

315
00:30:21,912 --> 00:30:24,745
我将挂如果我出去我的路对于任何杂狗狗。
I'll be hanged if I go out of my way for any cur dog.

316
00:30:25,448 --> 00:30:27,883
一个人应该做自己认为是最好的。
A man ought to do what he thinks is best.

317
00:30:41,097 --> 00:30:42,998
退出挡住了门。
Quit blocking the door.

318
00:30:47,103 --> 00:30:48,695
你从哪里搞到的?
Where did you get this?

319
00:30:49,406 --> 00:30:52,000
- 半个天南的双峰的骑。 - 如何?
- Half a day's ride south of Twin Buttes. - How?

320
00:30:52,209 --> 00:30:54,677
把它从几个印度人,阿帕奇人。
Took it off a couple of Indians, Apaches.

321
00:30:54,945 --> 00:30:57,106
走狗的Mescaleros住宿。
Running Dog Lodge of the Mescaleros.

322
00:30:57,380 --> 00:31:00,508
Mescaleros上升,太。 让所有Apache小屋。
Mescaleros are up, too. That makes all the Apache lodges.

323
00:31:00,617 --> 00:31:05,418
说,虽然我是南,没有移民得到从北方盆地?
Say, while I was south, did any settlers get in from the north basin?

324
00:31:05,522 --> 00:31:06,922
一些,过去的几周。
A few, the last couple of weeks.

325
00:31:07,023 --> 00:31:10,015
漂亮的女人,公平,一个男孩约六?
Handsome woman, fair, with a boy about six?

326
00:31:10,126 --> 00:31:12,560
没有,大多是中或老人。
No, mostly middle-aged or elderly people.

327
00:31:12,796 --> 00:31:15,287
得到一些睡眠,车道,用我的帐篷。
Get some sleep, Lane, use my tent.

328
00:31:15,566 --> 00:31:16,690
谢谢你！
Thank you.

329
00:31:25,542 --> 00:31:29,103
当你睡觉,我将移动你的可能的人选到我帐篷。
While you're sleeping, I'll move your possibles over to my tent.

330
00:31:31,014 --> 00:31:33,346
皮特・布里顿是侦察与C队伍。
Pete Britton was scouting with C troop.

331
00:31:33,884 --> 00:31:38,651
冬用旧皮特曾经的鸿沟。坏脾气的家伙。
Wintered with old Pete once up on the Divide. Ornery cuss.

332
00:31:39,321 --> 00:31:41,789
他们印度人你带,彭南特开门营业的。
Them indians you took that pennant offen.

333
00:31:41,925 --> 00:31:43,825
- 死印度人吗? - 最后。
- Dead Indians? - Finally.

334
00:31:59,006 --> 00:32:00,906
- 你好,皮特。 - 嗨,本州。
- Hi, Pete. - Hi, Hondo.

335
00:32:01,008 --> 00:32:03,136
伤了我的心,当我听到你做的。
Broke my heart when I heard you made it.

336
00:32:03,245 --> 00:32:06,408
你知道你开始反对人民行动党这所谓的威士忌?
Your pap know you started out against this so-called whiskey?

337
00:32:06,515 --> 00:32:07,880
我没见过他一个月。
I ain't seen him for a month.

338
00:32:07,982 --> 00:32:10,178
我知道你没有。来这里,我得到了一个消息给你。
I know you haven't. Come here, I got a message for you.

339
00:32:10,284 --> 00:32:12,775
离开他,本州,我无法使没有钱球探。
Leave him be, Hondo, I can't make no money scouting.

340
00:32:12,888 --> 00:32:15,412
噢,这些其他的家伙会原谅你。在吧台上过来。
Aw, these other fellows'll excuse you. Come on over at the bar.

341
00:32:15,524 --> 00:32:19,323
我不会。我走了100美元。
I won't. I'm out almost $100.

342
00:32:19,827 --> 00:32:22,991
- 数字,水牛在游戏中。-等待一分钟。
- That figures, with Buffalo in the game. - Wait a minute.

343
00:32:23,865 --> 00:32:25,925
这些衬衫都难。
These shirts are hard to come by.

344
00:32:31,572 --> 00:32:33,905
- 你怎么打我? - 因为我知道你。
- What'd you hit me for? - 'Cause I know you.

345
00:32:34,008 --> 00:32:35,168
皮革它。
Leather it.

346
00:32:37,779 --> 00:32:39,542
不,不要皮它。
No, don't leather it.

347
00:32:48,689 --> 00:32:51,157
难怪他们阿帕奇人叫他 Emberato。
No wonder them Apaches call him <i>Emberato.</i>

348
00:32:51,259 --> 00:32:53,227
- 这意味着什么呢? - 坏脾气。
- What does it mean? - Bad temper.

349
00:32:59,066 --> 00:33:00,966
我应该让他拍你。
I should've let him shoot you.

350
00:33:01,335 --> 00:33:04,827
这是我第二次已经彻底打败,说大话的无用的…
That's the second time I've tangled with that mouthy no-good<i>...</i>

351
00:33:05,473 --> 00:33:08,806
- 他叫什么名字? - 自称劳,艾德劳。
- What's his name? - Calls himself Lowe, Ed Lowe.

352
00:33:19,319 --> 00:33:20,480
约翰尼。
Johnny.

353
00:33:26,693 --> 00:33:28,389
约翰尼!
Johnny!

354
00:33:40,875 --> 00:33:42,171
妈妈。
Mommy.

355
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:49,812
嗨,妈妈。维托利奥说我会成为一个好Apache。
Hi, Mommy. Vittorio says I'll make a good Apache.

356
00:33:50,450 --> 00:33:54,148
我认为… 我不知道他是和你在一起,我什么都没听说。
I thought<i>...</i> I didn't know he was with you, I didn't hear anything.

357
00:33:54,488 --> 00:33:57,184
- Apache没有制造噪音。 - 看看他给我。
- Apache no make noise. - Look what he gave me.

358
00:33:57,290 --> 00:34:00,657
- 这是洛奇令牌。他的 - 这是非常漂亮的,谢谢你。
- It is lodge token. His. - It's very pretty, thank you.

359
00:34:01,262 --> 00:34:02,695
他会骑好。
He will ride well.

360
00:34:03,730 --> 00:34:05,220
和他没有害怕。
And he no afraid.

361
00:34:06,366 --> 00:34:09,301
- 我跟你妈妈,去房子。 - 是的,维托利奥。
- I speak with your mother, go to house. - Yes, Vittorio.

362
00:34:12,839 --> 00:34:14,500
旅馆应该有男人。
Lodge should have man.

363
00:34:15,108 --> 00:34:18,805
- 我的丈夫将家里现在任何一天。 - 我不这么认为。
- My husband will be home any day now. - I no think so.

364
00:34:19,180 --> 00:34:20,771
我认为他死了。
I think he dead.

365
00:34:27,922 --> 00:34:29,980
小战士应该有父亲。
Small Warrior should have father.

366
00:34:44,404 --> 00:34:46,565
看,军士,就像我告诉你。
See, Sergeant, just like I told you.

367
00:34:47,040 --> 00:34:50,373
这是我的马,好吧。有我的品牌:“e l“艾德劳。
That's my horse, all right. Got my brand on it: "E.L." Ed Lowe.

368
00:34:50,477 --> 00:34:52,001
他说什么真的吗?
What he says true?

369
00:34:52,112 --> 00:34:54,706
- 是的,那是他的马。-你在哪里得到他吗?
- Yeah, that's his horse. - Where'd you get him?

370
00:34:54,848 --> 00:34:58,011
从自己的农场,我就带他回来。
From his ranch, that's where I'm taking him back.

371
00:34:58,785 --> 00:35:00,184
这就是他能接他。
That's where he can pick him up.

372
00:35:00,287 --> 00:35:03,517
但这是印度的领土,严格的订单将在那里与任何白人。
But that's Indian territory, strict orders against any Whites going in there.

373
00:35:03,623 --> 00:35:07,718
你知道吗,乔,我得到了一个坏的耳朵。我听不见你说的什么。
You know something, Joe, I got a bad ear. I can't hear a thing you're saying.

374
00:35:16,469 --> 00:35:18,403
难道你会喜欢指控他吗?
Aren't you gonna prefer charges against him?

375
00:35:18,505 --> 00:35:21,065
他可能是一个意思,脾气不好的,儿子的任何你想叫他……
He may be a mean, ornery, son-of-anything-you-wanna-call-him...

376
00:35:21,174 --> 00:35:22,731
但他不是马贼。
but he ain't no horse thief.

377
00:35:22,842 --> 00:35:25,902
和我不会叫他一个,他的脸和他的背。
And I'm not gonna call him one, to his face or his back.

378
00:35:40,026 --> 00:35:41,492
你呆在这儿。
You stay here.

379
00:35:55,909 --> 00:35:58,639
我以为Apache总是沉默。
I thought the Apache were always silent.

380
00:35:58,944 --> 00:36:02,436
不是当他们寻求女人。你选择一个。
Not when they seek squaw. You pick one.

381
00:36:02,916 --> 00:36:04,008
什么?
What?

382
00:36:04,583 --> 00:36:05,948
不太好,小战士……
It's not good for Small Warrior...

383
00:36:06,051 --> 00:36:08,849
没有父亲教他如何成为男人。
to be without father to teach him how to be man.

384
00:36:10,689 --> 00:36:13,123
这是我在叫埃米利亚诺・。
This is the one I was calling Emiliano.

385
00:36:13,625 --> 00:36:16,059
非常勇敢,已采取许多头皮。
Very brave, has taken many scalps.

386
00:36:16,795 --> 00:36:21,232
他有六匹马,和两个squaws,但是一个老和很快就会死。
He has six horses, and two squaws, but one old and will soon die.

387
00:36:24,471 --> 00:36:25,801
他的好猎手。
He's good hunter.

388
00:36:26,171 --> 00:36:27,867
从来没有饿,他的窝棚。
Never hungry, his wickiup.

389
00:36:29,875 --> 00:36:32,105
这是一个叫做Kloori是谁。
This is one who is called Kloori.

390
00:36:34,813 --> 00:36:36,974
他有十匹马,一个女人。
He has ten horses, one squaw.

391
00:36:38,717 --> 00:36:41,652
Sachito,勇敢的战士,许多马。
Sachito, brave warrior, many horses.

392
00:36:43,355 --> 00:36:47,052
没有多少squaws击败,唱得很大声。
Not much beat squaws, sings very loud.

393
00:36:56,035 --> 00:36:59,596
- 男孩,去站在我的马。 - 是的,维托利奥。
- Boy, go stand by my horse. - Yes, Vittorio.

394
00:37:02,841 --> 00:37:06,436
小战士从来没有看到眼泪,Apache不哭泣。
Small Warrior never to see tears, Apache does not weep.

395
00:37:07,146 --> 00:37:09,842
首席,你不能让我这样做,我结婚了。
Chief, you can't make me do this, I'm married.

396
00:37:09,948 --> 00:37:12,279
你是傻瓜,你的男人死了。
You are fool, your man dead.

397
00:37:12,418 --> 00:37:16,353
很快来种植雨。如果你的男人回家,然后,好。
Soon come planting rain. If your man come home by then, good.

398
00:37:16,488 --> 00:37:18,590
如果不是,你把Apache勇敢。
If not, you take Apache brave.

399
00:37:27,332 --> 00:37:29,732
记住,时间种植雨。
Remember, time of planting rain.

400
00:37:41,246 --> 00:37:43,111
他有点深入印度领土。
He's getting kind of deep into Indian territory.

401
00:37:43,214 --> 00:37:44,442
,我们也是。
And so are we.

402
00:37:45,084 --> 00:37:47,847
你的叫声吗?你得到报酬优厚。
What are you squawking for? You're getting well paid.

403
00:37:48,386 --> 00:37:52,618
他会使营很快。不要让机会在他之后,我们会回头。
He'll be making camp pretty soon. Don't get a chance at him then, we'll turn back.

404
00:38:27,692 --> 00:38:29,557
安静的,山姆,我听到他们。
Quiet, Sam, I hear them.

405
00:38:41,372 --> 00:38:42,737
来吧,山姆。
Come on, Sam.

406
00:38:48,579 --> 00:38:50,342
这是他的营地,所有权利。
That's his camp, all right.

407
00:39:01,358 --> 00:39:04,122
步枪的消失,必须寻找营地肉。
Rifle's gone, must be out looking for camp meat.

408
00:39:45,402 --> 00:39:48,964
- 你是好的,你不是受伤了。 - 这个锡版照相法救了我。
- You're all right, you're not hurt bad. - This tintype saved me.

409
00:39:57,547 --> 00:39:58,947
做的那件事。
That did it.

410
00:39:59,549 --> 00:40:02,781
现在,我们之间每一个Apache和牧场会接到通知。
Now, every Apache between us and the ranch will be alerted.

411
00:40:03,887 --> 00:40:05,548
他们会让我们切断。
They'll have us cut off.

412
00:40:05,922 --> 00:40:08,720
不,没人在我们和Seddon堡。
No, there's nobody between us and Fort Seddon.

413
00:44:28,783 --> 00:44:30,273
打败它,山姆!
Beat it, Sam!

414
00:44:38,192 --> 00:44:40,922
- 白人了解Apache。 - 一个小。
- White man understand Apache. - A little.

415
00:44:41,394 --> 00:44:43,295
他现在知道他是如何死的。
He know now how he die.

416
00:44:43,564 --> 00:44:45,930
你贴头皮,展示了很多政变
Your coup stick shows many scalps.

417
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:49,328
是的,很多。很快,你。
Yes, many. Soon, you.

418
00:44:49,503 --> 00:44:50,970
人的头皮会从那里。
Man's scalp would look out of place there.

419
00:44:51,072 --> 00:44:54,336
你把所有你从squaws,幼儿和狗。
You took all yours from squaws, papoose, and dogs.

420
00:44:56,844 --> 00:44:59,539
你的旅馆应该是真正的为你骄傲。
Your lodge should be real proud of you.

421
00:45:08,289 --> 00:45:11,224
你需要长时间死亡。
You will take long time die.

422
00:45:32,112 --> 00:45:34,046
士兵在哪里,白色男人?
Where are soldiers, White man?

423
00:45:34,148 --> 00:45:36,547
- 有多少? - 我不知道,维托利奥。
- How many? - I don't know, Vittorio.

424
00:45:36,650 --> 00:45:37,982
你知道我的名字吗?
You know my name?

425
00:45:38,084 --> 00:45:41,350
我看到你曾经在米德堡条约理事会。
I saw you once at the Treaty Council at Fort Meade.

426
00:45:41,454 --> 00:45:42,546
该条约。
The treaty.

427
00:45:52,032 --> 00:45:55,126
该条约是喜欢沙沙作响的风的白人男子。
The treaty was like rustle of wind to White man.

428
00:45:55,702 --> 00:46:00,139
- 现在你告诉,士兵? - 这,我不知道。
- Now you tell, where are soldiers? - This, I do not know.

429
00:46:01,107 --> 00:46:03,371
-帽子。士兵的帽子。 - 我曾经是一个士兵。
- Hat. Soldier hat. - I was once a soldier.

430
00:46:03,476 --> 00:46:05,569
为什么你在这里Apache土地吗?
Why you here Apache land?

431
00:46:06,479 --> 00:46:08,208
这是我能知道的。
This is for me to know.

432
00:46:41,581 --> 00:46:44,879
我告诉你说侮辱我的首领这一套。
I'm told you speak insults to this one of my chiefs.

433
00:46:47,587 --> 00:46:51,045
美洲狮尖叫的侮辱和很勇敢。
The cougar screams insults and is brave.

434
00:46:51,890 --> 00:46:55,588
一只狼咆哮的侮辱和是一个懦夫。
A coyote howls insults and is a coward.

435
00:46:55,995 --> 00:46:57,462
我们将看到。
We shall see.

436
00:46:57,997 --> 00:47:00,557
美洲狮或土狼。
Cougar or coyote.

437
00:47:01,533 --> 00:47:03,627
你会死在沉默中勇敢地……
You will die bravely in silence...

438
00:47:04,069 --> 00:47:07,095
或者你会像女人带来孩子嚎啕大哭……
or you will wail like woman bringing forth child...

439
00:47:07,574 --> 00:47:10,064
和哀求我们小马士兵正。
and cry out to us where pony-soldiers are.

440
00:48:00,826 --> 00:48:03,488
他声称血吧,你明白吗?
He claims the blood right, you understand?

441
00:48:03,896 --> 00:48:06,456
你的意思是,他说我拍他的哥哥吗?
You mean, he says I shot his brother?

442
00:48:08,634 --> 00:48:09,794
我理解。
I understand.

443
00:48:40,466 --> 00:48:43,025
这样的生活可能落干净。
So that life may ebb cleanly.

444
00:49:50,400 --> 00:49:53,734
忘记你的血液对或加入你的哥哥。
Forget your blood right or join your brother.

445
00:50:14,826 --> 00:50:16,816
你认为你买你现在的生活吗?
You think you buy your life now?

446
00:50:17,728 --> 00:50:19,059
我不认为。
I don't think.

447
00:50:19,630 --> 00:50:22,155
你可能是死是活,我们看到。
You may live or die, we see.

448
00:51:14,285 --> 00:51:15,479
印第安人。
Indians.

449
00:51:39,843 --> 00:51:41,208
这是你的男人吗?
Is this your man?

450
00:51:41,677 --> 00:51:44,203
说,这是你的男人吗?
Speak, is this your man?

451
00:51:44,814 --> 00:51:48,045
- 是的,这是我的丈夫。 - 白人…
- Yes, this is my husband. - White man...

452
00:51:50,954 --> 00:51:53,388
你住在Apache,这很好。
you lived with the Apache, that's good.

453
00:51:53,957 --> 00:51:55,948
你知道小战士应该教…
You know how Small Warrior should be taught that...

454
00:51:56,058 --> 00:51:59,255
他的儿子被尊敬的人叫窝棚维托利奥。
he be honored son of wickiup of one who's called Vittorio.

455
00:51:59,362 --> 00:52:02,728
看像鹰,请耐心,因为《海狸》……
Watch like the hawk, be patient as the beaver...

456
00:52:02,933 --> 00:52:05,457
勇敢,彪马,那他可能学好。
brave as puma, that he may learn well.

457
00:52:05,901 --> 00:52:07,199
知道它,然后……
Know it, then...

458
00:52:07,536 --> 00:52:10,938
或者你的死会死很久之前你欢迎。
or your dying will be long before you welcome death.

459
00:53:25,948 --> 00:53:27,916
- 更多的咖啡吗?-不,谢谢。
- More coffee? - No, thanks.

460
00:53:31,653 --> 00:53:34,588
- 你要做什么? - 要修理你的衬衫。
- What are you gonna do? - Gonna fix up your shirt.

461
00:53:35,391 --> 00:53:37,382
之前,我告诉你一些。
Not before I show you something.

462
00:53:44,466 --> 00:53:48,027
- 给你这是埃德? - 我把它从他的身体。
- Did Ed give you this? - I took it off his body.

463
00:53:49,138 --> 00:53:50,400
他死了。
He's dead.

464
00:53:53,108 --> 00:53:54,803
试图告诉你之前。
Tried to tell you before.

465
00:53:56,979 --> 00:53:58,708
可笑,我不惊讶。
Funny, I'm not surprised.

466
00:54:00,181 --> 00:54:03,413
也许是因为我一直都清楚,只是不愿承认自己。
Perhaps because I knew all along, just wouldn't admit it to myself.

467
00:54:03,519 --> 00:54:06,249
- 嗨, Emberato, 你没死,你呢? - 你好,约翰尼。
- Hi, <i>Emberato,</i> you didn't die, did you? - Hello, Johnny.

468
00:54:06,354 --> 00:54:07,379
小心。
Be careful.

469
00:54:07,489 --> 00:54:10,014
我想告诉你一些东西, Emberato。我的印度的象征。
I wanna show you something, <i>Emberato.</i> My Indian emblem.

470
00:54:10,125 --> 00:54:12,355
维托利奥给了我,没有他,妈妈?
Vittorio gave it to me, didn't he, Mom?

471
00:54:15,230 --> 00:54:20,030
- 他是一个伟大的喜欢约翰尼了。 - 或许救了你的命和矿山。
- He's taken a great liking to Johnny. - Probably saved your life and mine.

472
00:54:20,568 --> 00:54:23,059
印度人非常看重男性儿童的地方。
Indians place great value on male children.

473
00:54:23,338 --> 00:54:26,431
他们也将一个伟大的价值对死去的好。
They also place a great value on dying well.

474
00:54:28,077 --> 00:54:29,669
Ed死好了吗?
Did Ed die well?

475
00:54:30,511 --> 00:54:32,377
我把它放在我的枕头。
I keep it under my pillow.

476
00:54:34,015 --> 00:54:35,175
他死了好。
He died well.

477
00:54:36,751 --> 00:54:39,982
当约翰尼太老了,当他被告知……
When Johnny's old enough, when he has to be told...

478
00:54:41,155 --> 00:54:42,748
它会使他骄傲。
it will make him proud.

479
00:54:43,292 --> 00:54:47,159
在这里, Emberato。我是一个首席现在。这不是很美妙吗?
Here it is, <i>Emberato.</i> I'm a chief now. Isn't it wonderful?

480
00:54:51,899 --> 00:54:54,527
- 不是吗? - 是的,约翰尼。
- Isn't it? - Yes, Johnny.

481
00:55:30,337 --> 00:55:32,932
- 你妈妈在什么地方? - 选择豆瓣菜。
- Where's your mother? - Picking watercress.

482
00:55:33,207 --> 00:55:35,641
- 任何运气吗?今天早上 - 不是咬。
- Any luck? - Not a bite this morning.

483
00:55:36,978 --> 00:55:38,467
看到太阳在哪里?
See where the sun is?

484
00:55:39,180 --> 00:55:41,273
- 那里。 - 是的,在你的颈后。
- Up there. - Yeah, on the back of your neck.

485
00:55:41,382 --> 00:55:42,974
你投下影子。
You're casting a shadow.

486
00:55:43,083 --> 00:55:45,279
如果你能看到它,鱼可以看到它。
If you can see it, the fish can see it.

487
00:55:45,386 --> 00:55:48,946
总是与太阳鱼在你的脸。其他银行的这个地方。
Always fish with the sun in your face. The other bank's the place.

488
00:55:49,089 --> 00:55:52,958
- 也就是说,如果你想听我的看法。 - 天哪,Emberato,我想听听你的意见。
- That is, if you want my opinion. - Gosh, <i>Emberato,</i> I want your opinion.

489
00:55:53,261 --> 00:55:54,819
但是妈妈不让我去那边。
But Mama won't let me go over there.

490
00:55:54,928 --> 00:55:56,863
- 为什么不呢? - 我不会游泳。
- Why not? - I can't swim.

491
00:55:57,931 --> 00:56:00,126
- 你不能什么? - 我不会游泳。
- You can't what? - I can't swim.

492
00:56:00,268 --> 00:56:02,132
- 你多大了?- 6。
- How old are you? - Six.

493
00:56:13,747 --> 00:56:18,241
- 帮助他,他不会游泳。 - 时间他学习。每个人都应该游泳。
- Help him, he can't swim. - Time he learned. Everybody should swim.

494
00:56:20,254 --> 00:56:23,121
只是在你面前伸出,抓一把水。
Just reach out in front of you and grab a handful of water.

495
00:56:23,223 --> 00:56:24,919
把它回到你。
Pull it back towards you.

496
00:56:27,527 --> 00:56:30,189
不太快。这是我学会了。
Not too fast. That's the way I learned.

497
00:56:35,802 --> 00:56:38,499
- 我做了它, Emberato, 我做到了。 - 好的。
- I did it, <i>Emberato,</i> I did it. - Good.

498
00:56:39,172 --> 00:56:41,265
- 他怎么回来的? - 游泳。
- How will he get back? - Swim.

499
00:56:41,441 --> 00:56:42,966
嗯,他可能会被淹死。
Well, he might drown.

500
00:56:43,443 --> 00:56:45,911
- 那么,你去找他。 - 我不会游泳,要么。
- Well, then, you go get him. - I can't swim, either.

501
00:58:07,093 --> 00:58:08,583
安吉,有…
Angie, there's...

502
00:58:09,528 --> 00:58:12,657
一些我必须告诉你。我想告诉你。
something I've got to tell you. I tried to tell you.

503
00:58:13,399 --> 00:58:16,334
和它不会是容易的。 - 那就不要说吗。
- And it isn't going to be easy. - Then don't say it yet.

504
00:58:16,902 --> 00:58:18,460
看看月亮。
Just look at the moon.

505
00:58:20,307 --> 00:58:22,400
多么奇怪的看起来在这个季度。
How odd it looks in this quarter.

506
00:58:24,076 --> 00:58:27,842
当我还是个孩子的时候,我的母亲曾经告诉我这是一个跷跷板。
When I was a child, my mother used to tell me it was a teeter-totter.

507
00:58:29,682 --> 00:58:32,480
你知道的,倾斜的木板一个孩子玩。
You know, the tilted plank a child plays on.

508
00:58:33,419 --> 00:58:35,854
我想印度人有的话。
I suppose the Indians have a word for it.

509
00:58:36,622 --> 00:58:39,057
是的, bermarga。 这是种植的月亮。
Yeah, <i>bermarga.</i> It's the planting moon.

510
00:58:39,158 --> 00:58:41,991
印度人不会种植玉米,除非月球的那样。
Indians won't plant their corn unless the moon's like that.

511
00:58:42,094 --> 00:58:44,688
你喜欢生活在Apache,不是吗?
You liked living with the Apache, didn't you?

512
00:58:45,297 --> 00:58:47,528
安琪,我刚要告诉你这个。
Angie, I've just got to tell you this.

513
00:58:48,200 --> 00:58:49,758
我没有说谎。
I'm not much for lying.

514
00:58:49,902 --> 00:58:52,564
上次我在这里,在维给我吗?
The last time I was here, before Vittorio brought me?

515
00:58:52,671 --> 00:58:53,638
是的。
Yes.

516
00:58:53,739 --> 00:58:57,402
我骑马分派一些之后,然后来到登。
I rode dispatch some after that, then came to Seddon.

517
00:58:58,143 --> 00:58:59,474
有麻烦了。
There was trouble.

518
00:59:00,412 --> 00:59:01,674
我杀了一个人。
I killed a man.

519
00:59:05,617 --> 00:59:08,347
呆着别动。有人在那些柳树。
Stay still. Somebody in those willows.

520
00:59:10,456 --> 00:59:12,048
别开枪,白人。
Don't shoot, White man.

521
00:59:20,999 --> 00:59:23,661
小战士有刀。他睡与它。
Small Warrior has knife. He sleeps with it.

522
00:59:23,969 --> 00:59:26,028
- 你是在家里吗? - 在房子。
- You were in the house? - In house.

523
00:59:27,005 --> 00:59:30,634
窝棚空的地方没有儿子。我空的窝棚。
Wickiup empty place without sons. Mine empty wickiup.

524
00:59:31,143 --> 00:59:35,238
你最好告诉那个勇敢的回到河岸不要在水里走。
You better tell that brave back at the creek bank not to walk in the water.

525
00:59:35,347 --> 00:59:37,611
我差点杀了他几分钟前。
I almost killed him a few minutes ago.

526
00:59:43,855 --> 00:59:45,618
几乎把射击他。
Almost threw a shot at him.

527
00:59:45,857 --> 00:59:48,122
他很轻。将学习。
He very young. Will learn.

528
00:59:48,360 --> 00:59:50,987
- 如果他住。 - 你是Apache。
- Lf he lives. - You are Apache.

529
00:59:52,197 --> 00:59:54,994
现在,听我,小马士兵靠近。
Now, hear me, pony-soldiers are near.

530
00:59:55,534 --> 00:59:59,560
很快将战斗战斗记忆。他们会来这里第一。
Soon will be fought remembered fight. They will come here first.

531
01:00:00,405 --> 01:00:03,671
- 你不会跟他们一起去,白人。-我不会。
- You will not go with them, White man. - I will not.

532
01:00:04,009 --> 01:00:06,500
领袖会怀疑你的小马士兵。
Leader of pony-soldiers will question you.

533
01:00:07,245 --> 01:00:10,271
你会说你看过Apache落后西方。
You will say you have seen Apache trailing to the west.

534
01:00:11,616 --> 01:00:13,050
这个我不会做。
This I won't do.

535
01:00:14,786 --> 01:00:17,051
- 你不会吗?-我不会。
- You will not? - I will not.

536
01:00:19,657 --> 01:00:21,921
你有好男人,珍惜他。
You have good man, treasure him.

537
01:00:30,168 --> 01:00:32,636
他们安装了现在下来的孤峰。
They're mounting up now down by the butte.

538
01:00:32,737 --> 01:00:34,535
我没有听到一点声音。
I don't hear a thing.

539
01:00:34,806 --> 01:00:36,569
有八个我想说的,或者是9。
There's eight of them I'd say, or maybe nine.

540
01:00:36,674 --> 01:00:40,872
- 有什么东西在那些树。 - 那是一只松鼠。我们的谈话把他唤醒。
- There's something in those trees. - That's a squirrel. Our talking woke him up.

541
01:00:40,979 --> 01:00:43,708
他熄灭。其中有9个。
He's put out. There's nine of them.

542
01:00:44,582 --> 01:00:45,913
我爱你。
I love you.

543
01:00:48,486 --> 01:00:50,716
我想我不应该这样说的…
I suppose I shouldn't have said that...

544
01:00:50,822 --> 01:00:52,881
和我的丈夫死了那么短的时间。
with my husband dead so short a time.

545
01:00:52,990 --> 01:00:57,427
我不猜人的心灵得到任何一个日历。
I don't guess people's hearts got anything to do with a calendar.

546
01:01:08,039 --> 01:01:11,236
你是如此美好,拒绝谎言,维托利奥。
You were so wonderful, refusing to lie for Vittorio.

547
01:01:12,009 --> 01:01:14,602
他在考验我。印度人讨厌谎言。
He was testing me. Indians hate lies.

548
01:01:15,813 --> 01:01:18,406
我想我必须有同样的感觉…
And I guess I got to feel the same way...

549
01:01:19,283 --> 01:01:21,409
但是,偶尔一个小伙子必须……
but, once in a while a fella's got to...

550
01:01:21,619 --> 01:01:24,281
谎言如果它会让别人更容易。
lie if it'll make it easier on someone else.

551
01:01:47,645 --> 01:01:49,943
队伍,停止!
Troop, halt!

552
01:01:53,184 --> 01:01:54,650
准备下车。
Prepare to dismount.

553
01:01:55,619 --> 01:01:56,984
下马!
Dismount!

554
01:02:09,099 --> 01:02:12,591
女士,先生,我可以介绍我自己吗?中尉麦凯,队伍D,8日骑兵。
Madam and sir, may I present myself? Lt. McKay, Troop D, 8th cavalry.

555
01:02:12,703 --> 01:02:15,729
- 嗨,本州,你老客舱强盗。 - 嗨,浅黄色。
- Hi, Hondo, you old cabin robber. - Hi, Buff.

556
01:02:15,839 --> 01:02:17,773
中尉,这这是本州巷。
Lieutenant, this here is Hondo Lane.

557
01:02:18,108 --> 01:02:21,373
他赤手空拳一些和骑调度一些骑兵。
He's scouted some and ridden dispatch some for the cavalry.

558
01:02:21,711 --> 01:02:25,203
-我不认为我知道这个夫人。 - 这是罗伊女士,中尉。
- I don't reckon I know this here lady. - This is Ms. Lowe, Lieutenant.

559
01:02:25,315 --> 01:02:27,306
你人是幸运的。显然,维托利奥…
You people are lucky. Obviously, Vittorio...

560
01:02:27,417 --> 01:02:30,215
和他的变节的乐队刚刚发生不发现这个隐藏的山谷。
and his renegade band just happened not to find this hidden valley.

561
01:02:30,320 --> 01:02:32,618
-维托利奥是这里很多。 - 和你住吗?
- Vittorio's been here lots. - And you lived?

562
01:02:32,722 --> 01:02:34,417
一个男人站在维卓智是一家了?
One Ione man stood off Vittorio?

563
01:02:34,524 --> 01:02:37,721
没有男子站了Apache卓智是一家。他让我们住在这里。
No Ione man stands off the Apache. He lets us live here.

564
01:02:38,295 --> 01:02:40,786
有近100人死亡的定居者在盆地……
There are almost 100 dead settlers in the basin...

565
01:02:40,897 --> 01:02:42,865
通过这个懦弱的罪犯杀害。
scalped by this cowardly criminal.

566
01:02:42,966 --> 01:02:45,958
维托利奥可能是一个犯罪的书,我不知道。
Vittorio may be a criminal by the books, I don't know.

567
01:02:46,102 --> 01:02:48,536
但如果他是一个懦夫,它并没有出现但。
But if he's a coward, it hasn't showed up yet.

568
01:02:48,638 --> 01:02:50,764
- 阿门,兄弟。 - 我必须同意你,雷恩。
- Amen, brother. - I must disagree with you, Mr. Lane.

569
01:02:50,874 --> 01:02:52,774
他在我们面前跑了200英里。
He's run before us for 200 miles.

570
01:02:52,876 --> 01:02:55,674
印度人有一个故事告诉他们的轻人……
Indians have a story they tell their young ones...

571
01:02:56,012 --> 01:02:59,573
关于一个猎人追一只猫,他抓住了它。
about a hunter who chased a wild cat until he caught it.

572
01:02:59,683 --> 01:03:01,048
然后是反过来的。
Then it was the other way around.

573
01:03:01,151 --> 01:03:03,414
这个故事追溯到进一步比印度人。
The story goes back further than the Indians.

574
01:03:03,520 --> 01:03:07,012
它的最初归因于第一罗马军队进入鞑靼。
It's originally attributed to the first Roman army to enter Tartary.

575
01:03:07,122 --> 01:03:08,715
了一个泼妇的士兵叫着。
The soldier caught a Tartar and yelled out.

576
01:03:08,825 --> 01:03:11,259
警官叫回来他进来与他的囚犯。
The officer called back for him to come in with his prisoner.

577
01:03:11,361 --> 01:03:13,692
他回答说,“鞑靼人不让我。”
And he replied, "The Tartar won't let me."

578
01:03:14,631 --> 01:03:16,565
这是一个最喜欢的故事上校的玉米……
That was one of the favorite stories of Col. Mays...

579
01:03:16,666 --> 01:03:18,361
谁教骑兵战术点。
who teaches cavalry tactics at the Point.

580
01:03:18,468 --> 01:03:19,901
这个故事是全球。
The story is world-wide.

581
01:03:20,003 --> 01:03:22,301
你有多久没有那个学校,中尉?
How long have you been out of that school, Lieutenant?

582
01:03:22,404 --> 01:03:24,065
69毕业先生,类。
Graduated class '69, sir.

583
01:03:24,274 --> 01:03:25,797
这是70,不是吗?
This is '70, ain't it?

584
01:03:26,041 --> 01:03:30,069
我只是不能跟上。我为了得到一个日历,但是然后我忘记。
I just can't seem to keep up with the years. I meant to get a calendar, but then I forget.

585
01:03:30,180 --> 01:03:32,011
说,谁是美国的总统了吗?
Say, who's President of these United States now?

586
01:03:32,115 --> 01:03:33,139
尤利西斯・s・格兰特。
Ulysses S. Grant.

587
01:03:33,248 --> 01:03:36,480
你知道,我投票一次。我被调到独立投票时间周围。
You know, I voted once. I was down in Independence around voting time.

588
01:03:36,586 --> 01:03:40,249
和同伴过来给了我2美元如果我投票给一个名叫泰勒。
And a fellow come up to me and offered me $2 if I'd vote for a man named Taylor.

589
01:03:40,356 --> 01:03:41,846
和我喝的是...
And I was drinking<i>...</i>

590
01:03:41,991 --> 01:03:44,984
当时喝一点。和我...  $ 2没有持续...
drinking a little at the time. And I<i>...</i> The $2 didn't last<i>...</i>

591
01:03:45,094 --> 01:03:48,394
罗伊太太,莱恩先生,我的订单做一个扫描到双峰。
Mrs. Lowe, Mr. Lane, my orders are to make a sweep as far as Twin Buttes.

592
01:03:48,498 --> 01:03:51,466
我的男人会今晚露宿。我们将继续双峰明天……
My men'll bivouac here tonight. We'll go on to Twin Buttes tomorrow...

593
01:03:51,567 --> 01:03:54,058
明天晚上返回护送你和你的男孩到安全。
return tomorrow night to escort you and your boy out to safety.

594
01:03:54,169 --> 01:03:58,128
如果你原谅我,夫人,我必须看到我的男人是正确的。扎营
If you'll excuse me, madam, I must see that my men are properly encamped.

595
01:04:02,345 --> 01:04:04,540
很好,很轻。
Very nice and very young.

596
01:04:04,680 --> 01:04:07,012
他对可恶的肯定是,夫人。
He for doggone sure is, ma'am.

597
01:04:07,116 --> 01:04:10,415
- 你多久在这巡逻吗? - 这是20天。
- How long you been out on this patrol? - This is the 20th day.

598
01:04:10,520 --> 01:04:13,852
我们搜集了大约八个家庭回到那里,这是所有有离开。
We've rounded up about eight families back there, that's all there are left.

599
01:04:13,956 --> 01:04:16,016
我们会接他们出来的路上。
We're gonna pick them up on the way out.

600
01:04:16,392 --> 01:04:18,155
这里有许多头皮了,本州。
There've been many a scalp took, Hondo.

601
01:04:18,261 --> 01:04:20,524
- 你知道维托利奥,别你吗? - 我做。
- You know where Vittorio is, don't you? - I do.

602
01:04:20,863 --> 01:04:22,455
这个男孩中尉的捉你杀死了。
This boy Lieutenant's gonna get you killed.

603
01:04:22,564 --> 01:04:25,158
美国童子军已经得把这些受过教育的轻军官。
Us scouts has got to get these young officers educated.

604
01:04:25,268 --> 01:04:27,758
约翰尼,进去,开始为我的盘子。
Johnny, go in and set out the plates for me.

605
01:04:27,870 --> 01:04:30,065
本州,如果你的朋友想和我们一起吃, Mr...
Hondo, if your friend would like to eat with us, Mr<i>...</i>

606
01:04:30,172 --> 01:04:32,300
水牛吗? Mr...
Buffalo? Mr<i>...</i>

607
01:04:32,975 --> 01:04:35,535
我已经知道你8或10。你必须有一个姓。
I've known you for 8 or 10 years. You must have a last name.

608
01:04:35,644 --> 01:04:38,374
嗯,我当然有一个姓,你把我当成什么了?
